  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ProteaTakoradi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(i) Absorb the unmet demand for quality hotel of international standards in a major business district of Takoradi. (ii) Standards: Improve hotel standards in the 3 star segment. (iii) Skill transfer: Encourage the transfer of skills and expertise in hotel management to the local workforce.  (iv) South-South Investment: support a South/South investment in CAF region. (v) Employment: Direct and indirect employment for locals during construction and operations.  (vi) Revenues: Government revenue source through tax collection. (vii) Local supplies: local procurement of construction supplies, food and services throughout construction and operations.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Greenfield project involves the construction and operation of a 3 star hotel in Takoradi Ghana (the Project) by Alliance Estates Limited (the Sponsor). The hotel will be branded as a Protea Select managed by Protea International.  Facilities will include 132 rooms and suites, a restaurant and bar, meeting space for 130 people, a workout room and 78 parking spaces.</narrative>
  </description>
